    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "We can not estimate in the software how much disk is going to be needed as it varies a lot depending on your sync speed. Generally around 350 GB are needed for the initial sync, but I would suggest an ssd with at least 1 tb since the node grows quickly once it was synced. The node can not check if there is enough space before starting the download. But it will stop if the space wasn't enough. In the future such questions are better suited to the ethereum stackexchange https://ethereum.stackexchange.com/",
